title: Motherhead Bug & Sulfur Discography
description:
The full discography New York City locals Motherhead Bug and Sulfur. Between them, the groups sharded members with numerous musical acts such as: Antony and the Johnsons, Lubricated Goat, Rasputina, Cop Shoot Cop, Firewater, Railroad Jerk, Heroine Sheiks, Soul Coughing and Swans. Both projects were led by trombonist David Ouimet (formerly of Cop Shoot Cop) and were heavily influenced by gypsy and cabaret music. Both bands set the stage for future Eastern European influenced acts such as Firewater (which briefly featured Ouimet) and Gogol Bordello.
